Preheat your #oven to 220°C. Drain the @mozzarella{1} and tear it into pieces.

Pat it all dry with #kitchen paper{}, making sure you squeeze out as much liquid as possible.

Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{60%g}.

Pop the @plain naans{2} onto a #baking tray{}.

Divide the @marinara sauce{120%g} between them and spread with the back of a #spoon, leaving a 1cm border.

Top with the @chorizo{50%g}(diced) then sprinkle over the cheese.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until the cheese is golden and bubbling, ~{6-7%minutes}.

In the meantime, pop the @fresh pesto{50%g} into a #small bowl{} ready for dipping.

While the naanizzas cook, finish off the washing up and make yourself a cuppa!

When ready, remove the naanizzas from the oven and slide them onto a #cutting board{}.

Cut them into slices then transfer them to your plates.

Serve with the pesto crust dipper alongside. Enjoy!